Player_Black (to Proxy):

Based on the board diagram, one natural idea is to give the white king a forcing check so it remains stuck in the corner. One candidate is moving the queen from c2 to c1. From c1 the queen gives check along the first rank (since it controls b1, c1, d1, etc.), and the white king on a1—which can only try escaping via a2, b1, or b2—will find that b1 and b2 are covered by the queen’s line of attack. (A queen move to a2, for example, would be met by a capture by the white king, so that would not be acceptable.) 

Therefore, a solid move in this position is:

make_move c2c1
